],"type":"disc"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"}],"ancestors":["1342166155"],"parent":"1342166155","lastUpdate":"2024-10-21T15:52:30.000Z","metadata":{"markets":["All"],"_id":"67370358a2376d68c46dfee1"},"search":["Camshaft Timing Check/Adjust","Make sure the motorcycle is stabilised and adequately supported.","Do not support the motorcycle on any ancillary component, the exhaust system or any other non structural parts of the motorcycle frame.","A correctly supported motorcycle will help prevent it from falling.","Failure to follow the advice above could result in serious injury or death.","When turning the crankshaft at the front of the engine (clutch cover end) always turn anticlockwise.","When turning the crankshaft at the rear of the engine (alternator cover end) always turn clockwise.","Turning the crankshaft in the wrong direction may cause the camshaft drive chain to slip on the camshaft sprockets resulting in incorrect camshaft timing.","Perform the following operations:","Clutch Cover - Removal","Camshaft Cover - Removal","Camshaft Timing Check","Remove the spark plugs to reduce compression resistance when turning the engine.","Remove the crankshaft locking pin plug from the crankcase.","At the front of the engine, rotate the crankshaft anticlockwise using the bolt fitted to the end of the crankshaft until the two gear teeth with an alignment mark on each is visible and central in the hole for the crankshaft locking pin.","Crankshaft primary gear","Alignment marks","Check that the camshafts alignment marks on the sprocket end of the camshaft are pointing inwards. If they are pointing outwards, turn the crankshaft anticlockwise 360 degrees until the two gear teeth with an alignment mark on each is visible in the hole for the crankshaft locking pin.","Camshaft alignment marks","Exhaust camshaft","Inlet camshaft","The alignment mark on the flange of ","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin"," is in line with the gear tooth at the other end of the service tool. Use this alignment mark as a guide when inserting the service tool.","Insert ","service tool T3880501"," through the hole in the crankcase. Make sure the gear tooth on the service tool fits between the two teeth with the alignment marks.","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin","Alignment mark","Insert ","service tool T3880502"," into the camshaft slots. Make sure the tool is centrally located between the camshafts. ","T3880502 - Camshaft timing bar","Camshaft slots","With the camshaft alignment marks, at the sprocket end, pointing inwards and the camshaft timing bar in the slots of the camshaft, adjustment is not required.","If the camshaft timing bar will not fit into the camshaft slots, adjust the camshaft timing as described in the procedure below.","Camshaft Timing Adjustment (if required)","Loosen the two accessible camshaft sprocket fixings, do not remove at this stage.","Fixings","Remove ","service tool T3880501"," from the crankcase.","At the front of the engine, rotate the crankshaft anticlockwise 360 degrees using a suitable socket on the bolt fitted to the end of the crankshaft (do not use the water pump drive slot in the bolt to turn the engine). Loosen the two accessible camshaft sprocket fixings, do not remove at this stage.","Fixings","Turn the crankshaft anticlockwise 360 degrees until the two gear teeth with an alignment mark on each is visible in the hole for the crankshaft locking pin.","Crankshaft primary gear","Alignment marks","Check that the camshafts alignment marks on the sprocket end of the camshaft are pointing inwards. If they are pointing outwards, turn the crankshaft anticlockwise 360 degrees until the two gear teeth with an alignment mark on each is visible in the hole for the crankshaft locking pin.","The alignment mark on the flange of ","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin"," is in line with the gear tooth at the other end of the service tool. Use this alignment mark as a guide when inserting the service tool.","Insert ","service tool T3880501"," through the hole in the crankcase. Make sure the gear tooth on the service tool fits between the two teeth with the alignment marks.","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin","Alignment mark","Place suitable wedges between the camshaft sprockets and the crankcase, to hold the camshaft drive chain taut during removal of camshaft drive tensioner and the fitting of ","service tool T3880651",".","Remove the camshaft drive tensioner (see ","Camshaft Drive Chain Tensioner - Removal",").","Check that the camshaft drive chain is engaged around the camshaft drive sprocket on the crankshaft, the camshaft sprockets and is positioned against the tensioner blade.","Fit the ","service tool T3880651"," and tighten to ","16 Nm",".","T3880651 - Timing Chain Tensioner","The torque value stated is very important to accurate timing. Always use the correct value of ","0.6 Nm",", as set using ","T3880609 - Timing Torque Limiter",". Using an incorrect torque value will result in incorrect valve timing being set, or damage to the tensioner blade or other valve train components. Either condition may result in serious damage to the engine, reduced engine performance, or reduced fuel economy.","Using ","service tool T3880609"," tighten ","service tool T3880651"," to ","0.6 Nm",". ","T3880609 - Timing Torque Limiter","Turn the camshafts only to allow ","service tool T3880502"," to fit into the camshaft slots.","T3880502 - Camshaft timing bar","Camshaft slots","Check that the camshafts alignment marks on the sprocket end of the camshaft are pointing inwards.","Camshaft alignment marks","Exhaust camshaft","Inlet camshaft","Tighten the two accessible (uppermost) camshaft sprocket fixings to ","16 Nm",".","Fixings","Remove the wedges between the camshaft sprockets and the crankcase.","Remove ","service tool T3880502"," from the camshaft slots.","T3880502 - Camshaft timing bar","Camshaft slots","Remove ","service tool T3880501"," from the crankcase.","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin","Alignment mark","Always check that ","service tool T3880502"," has been removed before rotating the engine. Severe damage will result to the camshafts or ","service tool T3880502"," if engine rotation is attempted with the tool installed. ","Rotate the engine until the remaining two sprocket bolts are accessible.","Tighten the two remaining camshaft sprocket fixings to ","16 Nm",".","Make sure the two gear teeth with an alignment mark on each is visible in the hole for the crankshaft locking pin and install the ","service tool T3880501",".","Crankshaft primary gear","Alignment marks","The alignment mark on the flange of ","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin"," is in line with the gear tooth at the other end of the service tool. Use this alignment mark as a guide when inserting the service tool.","Insert ","service tool T3880501"," through the hole in the crankcase .Make sure the gear tooth on the service tool fits between the two teeth with the alignment marks.","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin","Alignment mark","With the camshaft alignment marks pointing inwards and the camshaft timing bar in the slots of the camshaft, adjustment is not required. Continue from step 23.","If the camshaft timing bar will not fit into the camshaft slots, repeat the camshaft timing adjustment procedure.","Insert ","service tool T3880502"," into the camshaft slots. Make sure that the tool is centrally located between the camshafts. ","T3880502 - Camshaft timing bar","Camshaft slots","Make sure the camshaft drive chain remains on the crankshaft sprocket when removing ","service tool T3880651"," and fitting the camshaft drive chain tensioner.","Maintain tension on the camshaft drive chain, release the tension on ","service tool T3880651"," and remove it.","Refit the timing chain tensioner, incorporating a new O-ring (see ","Camshaft Drive Chain Tensioner - Installation",".","Remove ","service tool T3880502","Remove ","service tool T3880501",".","Fit the crankshaft locking pin plug and tighten to ","33 Nm",".","Perform the following operations:","Camshaft Cover - Installation","Clutch Cover - Installation","Fuel Tank - Installation","Battery - Installation","Seat - Installation"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType04","createdAt":"2024-11-15T08:16:24.076Z","updatedAt":"2024-11-15T08:16:24.076Z","__v":0}